Consider the following programming problem related to dynamic programming:

Given a grid of n x m cells, find the minimum number of steps required to visit every cell in the grid.

This problem can be solved with dynamic programming. First, define a function that represents the minimum number of steps required to visit a grid:

minSteps(n, m) {
    if (n == 0 || m == 0) {
        return 0;
    }
    const steps = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (let j = 0; j < m; j++) {
            steps.push(i + ":" + j);
        }
    }
    function minStepsRecursive(n, m, steps) {
        if (n == 0 && m == 0) {
            return steps;
        }
        let minSteps = Infinity;
        for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (let j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                let step = i + ":" + j;
                if (step < minSteps) {
                    minSteps = step;
                }
            }
        }
        return minSteps;
    }
    return minStepsRecursive(n, m, steps);
}

Then, the solution for the problem can be obtained by calling the function on the grid:

minSteps(n, m);

